pr_body:
Updated version of #138.

#139 must be merged first (this one is built on top of #139 branch)

@sjagoe

First step to support repack for python 3.

The second step is updating enstaller to support those new arguments

@sjagoe

This method will allow nbextensions to easily register a new mime type and a renderer for that mime types.

Usage:

```js
var append_json = function (json, md, element) {
  var type = ‘application/json’;
  var toinsert = this.create_output_subarea(md, 'output_json rendered_html', type);
  this.keyboard_manager.register_events(toinsert);
  ReactDOM.render(React.createElement(JSONTree, {data: json}), toinsert[0])
  element.append(toinsert);
  return toinsert;
};
Object.getPrototypeOf(OutputArea).register_mime_type(‘application/json’, append_json, true);
```

See https://github.com/gnestor/notebook_json/tree/render-output for a working implementation  using this method.

- Docstrings;
- More specific variable names;
- Reduced some code repetition;

There are still a couple of warnings because `sentry` is constant but lower case, the catch-all except and the typing imports.

This replaces #287 with a new branch on this repo, and updated for DKPY2.x. The updates include the change to the way that the example is started and also change to using dronekit rather than droneapi.

The example has not been tested against DKPY2.x yet (build not working) and the example screen output when running is a "guess" at what it will look like under DKPY2.

@tcr3dr @mrpollo This can be merged.
